<item>
            <title>[FLINK-23893] Fine-grained resource allocation may fail depending on slot allocation order</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-23893</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fine-grained slot management is relatively simple in that it iterates over each registered TM in order for each required slot.&lt;br/&gt;
This means that you can pretty easily create scenarios where, depending on the slot order, the allocation of a slot may fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A trivial example, only using memory for conciseness:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 TMs with 3 MB of memory each&lt;br/&gt;
2 slot-sharing groups with parallelism=2 and the following requirements:&lt;br/&gt;
 1) 1 MB memory&lt;br/&gt;
 2) 2 MB memory&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If both sub-tasks of 1) are scheduled first on a single TM then the job cannot be scheduled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not terrible for this limitation to exist in the first version, but it should be &lt;em&gt;explicitly&lt;/em&gt; documented.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
